line_1: "For pleasures have their seasons, and their soils.
line_2: "But mix with art your pleasures, and your toils;

line_1: Sails unknown seas to unknown soils,
line_2: The man, who with undaunted toils

line_1: Nor heeds fierce suns, nor stubborn soils.
line_2: With thee, he pleas'd pursues his toils,

line_1: No self-assuming air her judgment soils;
line_2: Her sprightly wit no forward pertness spoils:
